article.headline: George Mason 71, Towson 59
article.story: TOWSON, Md. -- Darryl Monroe had 16 points and 10 rebounds, Cam Long added 13 points and George Mason beat Towson 71-59 on Wednesday night. Dre Smith scored 11 points for the Patriots (11-3, 4-0 Colonial Athletic Association), who have beaten the Tigers 13 straight times. George Mason has won three straight and nine of 10 overall. Josh Thornton scored 14 points and Tony Franklin 10 for Towson (7-9, 2-2), which was denied a season-high third straight victory. Junior Hairston grabbed 11 rebounds. Monroe was dominant inside early, scoring eight points as George Mason built an early 22-8 lead. The Tigers never got closer than 30-22 on Thornton's 3-pointer with 1:05 left in the first half. Towson finished with a 37-32 edge in rebounds, but shot only 20-for-52 from the field and 4-for-18 from 3-point range. The Patriots converted 17 Tiger turnovers into 20 points.
